NAME: head
DESCRIPTION:
Print the firsts [-n number] lines of a files named [file].
	Print the first 10 lines if [-n number] option is not given.

	Example to print the firsts 10 lines of a file named README.md.
		head README.md
	Example to print the firsts 2 lines of a file named README.md.
		head -n 2 README.md

	See also tail.
